+20 EECS UD (20 units)

________________________

40 units completed just through your requirements (assuming you don't have any unusual petitions/exceptions). 

Meaning you need 5 more units. These could be extra EE/CS/EECS courses or technical courses from engineering departments. These do not include graduate courses or "any course taken on a P/NP basis; courses numbered 24, 39, 84; BioE 100; ChemE 185; CS 70, C79, 195, H195; Des Inv courses (except Des Inv 15, 22, 23, 90E, 190E); Engin 125, 157AC, 180; IEOR 95, 172, 185, 186, 190 series, 191, 192, 195; ME 191AC, 190K, 191K."(source: https://engineering.berkeley.edu/academics/undergraduate-guide/degree-requirements/eecs). 

See @6706 for more
